# Voltage

In order to have [[61-Archive/20220408110703-current-flow|current flow]] between two points, we need to have **_voltage difference_** between two points.

symbol:: V

<!--SR:!2022-04-26,4,270-->

unit:: volt (V)

<!--SR:!2022-04-26,4,270-->

![../60-Meta-Attachments/2533a46da5506092fca101258d541164.png](data:image/png;base64,)

> [[61-Archive/20220411113840-node|!word]] Voltage
> The potential difference between two nodes of a circuit.

## Continuous Current Flow

- **+ve charge** moves from _+ve terminal_ to the _-ve terminal_, due to **_potential difference_**
- We need to move **+ve charge** from _-ve terminal_ back to the _+ve terminal_
- Vice versa.

> [!example]
> Two terminals of a [[61-Archive/20220221170305-battery|battery]] has different polarity and hence have potential difference.
> A [[61-Archive/20220221170305-battery|battery]] uses [[Chemical-Energy|chemical energy]] to move the [[61-Archive/20220408114349-electron|electrons]].

## Analogy

![../60-Meta-Attachments/bf466bae901c9caa8998ec54a59f86a3.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Ball flow inside a tube.

1. Tube has to be tilted and [[Gravitational-Force|gravitational force]] will make the balls flow.
2. The [[Gravitational-Potential-Energy|gravitational potential energy]] depends on the difference between the height of the two ends of the tube
